    <!-- Chosen Palette: Calm Medical Harmony -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The application is structured as a clinical workflow dashboard, guiding the user from initial diagnosis to long-term prognosis. This non-linear structure, using a sticky navigation bar and thematic sections, is chosen over the report's original format to provide rapid, task-oriented access to information. Key interactions include an interactive diagnostic criteria checklist, a pathophysiology timeline, a tabbed management toolkit, and data visualizations for etiology and outcomes. This design prioritizes clinical usability and quick reference, allowing practitioners to find relevant information based on their immediate needs rather than reading a linear document. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices:
        - Berlin Criteria (Table): Goal: Inform/Organize -> Method: Interactive Accordion (HTML/JS) -> Interaction: Click to expand/collapse criteria details -> Justification: Cleaner and more engaging than a static table, focuses user attention.
        - ARDS Etiology (Donut Chart): Goal: Show Proportions -> Method: Chart.js Donut Chart -> Interaction: Hover for tooltips with percentages -> Justification: Quickly conveys the most common causes of ARDS.
        - Pathophysiology Phases (Timeline): Goal: Show Process -> Method: Interactive Stepper (HTML/CSS/JS) -> Interaction: Click on a phase to view its detailed description -> Justification: Visualizes the temporal progression of the disease in a clear, digestible format.
        - PICS Prevalence (Bar Chart): Goal: Compare -> Method: Chart.js Bar Chart -> Interaction: Hover for exact prevalence percentages -> Justification: Effectively compares the long-term impact across physical, cognitive, and mental health domains.
        - Management Toolkit (Tabs): Goal: Organize -> Method: Tabbed Interface (HTML/JS) -> Interaction: Click tabs to switch between management pillars -> Justification: Organizes a large volume of complex treatment information into logical, manageable sections.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
